OL,3,CWhere is the #470,000 fine Birmingham
OL,4,CCity Council has paid itself going?
OL,6,FHistorically, Birmingham City Council
OL,7,Fhas owned and operated a large fleet
OL,8,Fof more than 1,100 vehicles, many of
OL,9,Fwhich were not compliant with the
OL,10,FClean Air Zone, and therefore subject
OL,11,Fto paying the daily fee.
OL,13,FIn a statement, the council said it's
OL,14,Fworking to solve the problem: "Over
OL,15,Fthe last 12 months an extensive
OL,16,Freplacement programme has been put in
OL,17,Fplace so that the entire waste, street
OL,18,Fcleansing and grounds fleet is now
OL,19,Ffully compliant with the Clean Air
OL,20,FZone.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1780078266
OL,3,CWhere is the #470,000 fine Birmingham
OL,4,CCity Council has paid itself going?
OL,6,F"Further changes have also been made
OL,7,Fto other vehicles which have either
OL,8,Fbeen decommissioned or replaced with
OL,9,Felectric alternatives.
OL,11,F"Of all the fleet vehicles that the
OL,12,FCity Council own, 142 vehicles remain
OL,13,Fnon-compliant with the Clean Air Zone
OL,14,Fbut these are already under review and
OL,15,Fare on track to be removed from the
OL,16,Ffleet.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/5
