OL,3,CWhere is the #470,000 fine Birmingham
OL,4,CCity Council has paid itself going?
OL,6,F"The council's policy is that drivers
OL,7,Fare responsible for paying any fines
OL,8,Fthey incur themselves using their own
OL,9,Fvehicles for work, unless there is
OL,10,Fevidence that the penalty resulted
OL,11,Ffrom a council-related issue or error."
OL,13,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,14,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,15,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,16,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,17,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,18,Fbelow...
